ous, and ethnic struggles that infuse the peasant-worker milieu, as traditional representations of reality are pitted against bureaucratic definitions and formulas emanating from Church, state, and market institutions. In addition to providing a general theoretical framework for the analysis of peasant-worker society and culture, Cultural Disenchantments is the first anthropological study of Friuli to be published in English. As such, it elaborates on the historical insights developed by Carlo Ginzburg in his famous study of sixteenthcentury agrarian cults and folk traditions in Friuli.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aPeasantszItalyzCividale del Friuli Region. 0aWorking classzItalyzCividale del Friuli Region. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aBottenicco.  aBretell, Caroline.  aCarrasco, Pedro.  aCividale del Friuli.  aConsiglio communale.  aDouglass, William.  aDublin, Thomas.  aDurkheim, Emile.  aEley, Geoff.  aFriuli region.  aGramsci, Antonio.  aGuiotto, Luigi.  aHabermas, Jurgen.  aHansen, Edward.  aHennis, Wilhelm.  aHolmes, Douglas.  aInquisition.  aKertzer, David.  aLe Play, Frédéric.  aMarx, Karl.  aMoimacco.  aMovimento Friuli.  aSilverman, Sydel.  aVenice.  aaccountancy.  aagricultural production.  abenandanti.  abraccianti.  acapitalism.  acontracts.  acossans.  acultural disenchantment.  aethnicity.  aevil eye.  afamei.  afamily.  afascism.  afeudalism.  afieldwork.  agastaldi.  aindustry.  alatifondi.  aoperai.  apadroni.  apatronage.  arationalization.  areification.  asocial security.  atenancy.  awage earning.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyter